      <title>Version 0.5.98</title>
      <description><![CDATA[
        <style>
          body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.5; padding: 12px; }
          h2 { font-size: 16px; margin: 0 0 12px 0; }
          h3, h4 { font-size: 14px; margin: 12px 0 6px 0; }
          li { margin: 4px 0; }
          ul { padding-left: 20px; }
          .source { margin-top: 16px; padding-top: 8px; font-size: 11px; }
          @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
            body { color: #e0e0e0; background: #1a1a1a; }
            h2, h3, h4 { color: #fff; }
            .source { border-top: 1px solid #333; color: #888; }
            a { color: #58a6ff; }
          }
          @media (prefers-color-scheme: light) {
            body { color: #333; background: #fff; }
            h2, h3, h4 { color: #111; }
            .source { border-top: 1px solid #ddd; color: #999; }
            a { color: #0366d6; }
          }
        </style>
        <h2>What's New in 0.5.98</h2>
        <h3>Improvements</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Enhanced Sample Info dialog</strong> — Source-specific labels ("YouTube Page" / "Freesound Page"), clickable uploader profiles, clickable Freesound tags and search phrases, and YouTube video descriptions now display correctly</li>
          <li><strong>Download behavior help</strong> — The ? info button next to "Use Entire Sample" is now always visible, with context-aware help explaining duration settings (when disabled) or All/Clip/Skip options (when enabled)</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Bug Fixes</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Fixed YouTube samples incorrectly showing "Freesound Page" label in Sample Info</li>
          <li>Fixed Freesound uploader, tags, and search phrase not being clickable links</li>
          <li>Fixed YouTube video descriptions not displaying in Sample Info</li>
        </ul>
      ]]></description>
